benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/emails/{email} - Delete email from account

covered: DELETE - Valid Deletion: Successful deletion of an email from an account (TC01, TC02, TC12, TC13, TC17, TC18).
DELETE - Non-Existent Resource: Proper handling for non-existent account or email (TC03, TC04, TC09).
DELETE - Concurrency: Handling of concurrent deletions for the same email (TC15).
DELETE - Validation: Input validation for accountId and email formats (TC05, TC06, TC16).
DELETE - Authorization: Handling missing and invalid authorization headers (TC07, TC10).
DELETE - Query Parameters: Unsupported or extra query parameters do not break deletion (TC08).
DELETE - Server Error Handling and Resilience: Service unavailability and recovery (TC11, TC19).
DELETE - Edge Cases: Very large and minimal-length emails (TC12, TC13).
DELETE - Regression: Uppercase email support and backward compatibility (TC17, TC18).
gaps: Soft Deletes: No tests for soft-delete semantics (e.g., a deleted flag) separate from removed data.
Authorization: No test for 403 Forbidden due to insufficient permissions.
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate-limiting/throttling on delete.
Caching: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) on delete responses.
Internal Server Error coverage: Only 503 tested; no explicit 500 Internal Server Error scenario.
recommendations: Add a 403 Forbidden test to cover insufficient permissions for deletion.
Add rate-limiting tests to verify throttling behavior under load.
Add caching tests to validate ETag/Cache-Control headers (for delete) and cache invalidation.
Add a 500 Internal Server Error test to cover generic server failures.
Add more concurrency stress tests and longer-run performance baselining.
Consider a dedicated regression test to ensure consistent behavior with partial inputs and unusual header combos.
